Preconditions:
- The input grid must not be null.
- The input grid must have at least one row and one column.
- The values in the grid must be integers between 1 and 4.

Postconditions:
- The method returns an integer representing the minimum cost to make the grid have at least one valid path.
- The grid may be modified with a cost of 1 to change the signs on the cells.
- The modified grid must have at least one valid path from the upper left cell to the bottom-right cell.
- The modified grid may have multiple valid paths, and the minimum cost is the cost of the path with the fewest sign changes.